{
  "texts": [
    "Blair-Stanek et al. (2023) used up to 10-shot CoT prompting and also found, again contrary to Kojima et al. (2023) 's results, this was unhelpful in their experimental context.",
    "In general, their prompts were much more complex: for example, in their \"4-shot dynamic prompting\" context, they included the four most similar training cases and labelled the text of the case (which they also provided in full) with the \"premise\", the \"hypothesis\", and the \"answer\".",
    "Having to prepare prompts in this way may not actually save lawyers time.",
    "Notably, Choi et al. (2023) specifically asked ChatGPT not to \"fabricate\" any facts, and it followed this instruction.",
    "Overall, these findings suggest prompt engineering is much more of an art than an exact science."
  ]
}